    "creation_date" : 1446783872,
    "answer_id" : 33559474,
    "question_id" : 31215452,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you'd like to have your JAVA_HOME recognised by intellij, you can do one of these:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Start your intellij from terminal /Applications/IntelliJ IDEA 14.app/Contents/MacOS (this will pick your bash env variables)</li>\n<li>Add login env variable by executing: <code>launchctl setenv JAVA_HOME \"/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk1.8.0_60.jdk/Contents/Home\"</code></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>As others have answered you can ignore JAVA_HOME by setting up SDK in project structure.</p>\n"
  }, {
